# Normalize line endings. LF is canonical in the repo and on checkout for every
# platform (CI, Docker, and WSL are all LF-native). This prevents CRLF churn and
# the "phantom modified files" that appear when the same checkout is viewed from
# both Windows (autocrlf) and WSL/Linux git.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit (redundant with the rule above, kept for clarity).
*.sh text eol=lf
Dockerfile text eol=lf

# Binary assets: never apply end-of-line conversion to these.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.webp binary
*.ttf binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.pdf binary
*.gz binary
*.zip binary
*.db binary
